al data, whereas the diffusion coefficient of helium is in the range\nof 1 {\\AA} 2 /ps and tends to decrease as pressure increases. The radii of\nhelium drops have been found to be between 1 and 2 {\\AA}.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Jul 2021 16:50:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-21"}
