-3.1}$ to $10^{-3.4}-10^{-4.0}$ Hz, and mean strain from\n$10^{-17.2}$ to $10^{-16.3}-10^{-15.3}$. Finally, we show that after including\na merger delay and associated $M_{\\rm{BH}}$ growth, mergers still tend to lie\non the typical $M_{\\rm{BH}}-M_*$ relation, but with an increased likelihood of\nan undermassive black hole.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Jul 2021 18:00:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-20"}
